org.oucs.oxpoints.entities.pool
Class OxPointsEntityPool

java.lang.Object
  org.oucs.oxpoints.entities.pool.OxPointsEntityPool

public class OxPointsEntityPool
extends java.lang.Object

A collection of OxPointsEntitys that for some reason belong together.

An OxPointsEntityPool can be seen as a collection of OxPointsEntitys that have something in common. OxPointsEntityPools can be created by simply adding entities "by hand" or they can be automatically created from an OxPointsSnapshot or a Jena Model.

The automatic creation is configured using a OxPointsEntityPoolConfiguration object.

Version:
0.1
Author:
Arno Mittelbach
See Also:

filterEntities

public void filterEntities(java.util.Collection<EntityFilter> filters)
Removes entities that do not fulfill all filter criteria.

OxPointsEntitys in this pool might still hold references to removed entities after filtering. Filtered entities are only removed from the pool, not from other entities in the pool.

Parameters:
filters - The collection of EntityFilters.

removeEntity

public void removeEntity(OxPointsEntity entity)
Removes an entity from this pool.

The entity will only be removed from the pool. Even if any other entity in this pool holds a reference to the deleted entity, that reference will not be deleted.

Parameters:
entity - The entity that is to be deleted.
